      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "In most cases there is a clear distinction between the two types of"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "commands.  A line command affects the one or more lines that you place"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "the command on.  For example, marking a line with \"d\" and pressing the"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Enter key will delete the marked line."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Primary commands, on the other hand, may affect the entire file.  The"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "FIND command, for example, will search the entire file to locate the"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "specified search argument."
